headline: Best Buy ups sales outlook heading into holiday shopping season
summary: Best Buy raised its profit and sales expectations ahead of the holiday shopping ramp-up on Black Friday after a strong third quarter.  Comparable-store sales at the nation's largest consumer electronics chain rose 2.7%, fueled by computing, gaming and mobile phones.  The strong quarter is an encouraging sign for Best Buy, which like almost all U.S. companies, has spent months navigating an uncertain economic environment as President Donald Trump imposes wide-ranging tariffs on imports.

headline: Best Buy’s (NYSE:BBY) Q3 CY2025: Beats On Revenue
summary: Electronics retailer Best Buy (NYSE:BBY) reported Q3 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 2.4% year on year to $9.67 billion. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $41.8 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.40 per share was 6.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Best Buy tops Q3 earnings estimates, saw sales rise by 2.7%
summary: Electronics retailer Best Buy (BBY) is lifting its full-year outlook after beating third quarter earnings and revenue estimates. The chain store saw same-store sales rise by 2.7% in the quarter, above the 1.6% metric forecasted by Wall Street. Yahoo Finance senior retail reporter Brooke DiPalma comes on The Morning Brief to discuss Best Buy's quarterly figures and what it says about the state of the consumer amid personal device upgrade cycles. headline: Retail earnings in focus with Best Buy leading the way
summary: Best Buy (BBY) posted third quarter results that beat Wall Street estimates and raised its full-year outlook, setting the stage for the retailer as it heads into the crucial holiday shopping season. Kohl's (KSS) forecast a smaller drop in sales and bigger profit for the full year, as the U.S. department-store operator banks on new collections and promotions to drive demand during the holiday season, sending its shares surging in the premarket. Meanwhile, share of Dick's Sporting Goods (DKS) fell sharply before the opening bell despite raising its outlook. Investors are more worried about the cost of turning around its recent purchase of Foot Locker. For more live coverage of the markets, watch the full episode of Market Sunrise and visit Yahoo Finance.

headline: Retail sales, Alphabet chips for Meta, Dick's earnings: 3 Things
summary: US stock futures (ES=F, NQ=F, YM=F) are mixed in Tuesday's pre-market session after September's retail sales data rose by 0.2% (below economists' forecasts for 0.4% in that month), while September PPI (Producer Price Index) rose 0.3% in the month and 2.7% year-over-year. According to a report from The Information, Meta Platforms (META) is in talks to spend billions on AI chips developed by Alphabet (GOOG, GOOGL), putting the Google parent company in a position to directly compete with semiconductor giant Nvidia (NVDA). Retailers Dick's Sporting Goods (DKS), Best Buy (BBY), Alibaba (BABA, 9988.HK), and Kohl's (KSS) are all out with earnings results this morning. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief.
